ctional analysis, to support counselors in playing a more activist role in helping to change that context. Brown encourages counselors to not only understand the social problems that contribute to personal challenges faced by clients but to also raise awareness and promote change.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Jun 2021) 0aCommunity psychology. 0aCross-cultural counseling. 0aCultural pluralismxPsychological aspects. 0aSocial justice. 0aSocial problemsxPsychological aspects. 4aCoursebook. 7aEDUCATION / Educational Psychology.2bisacsh40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781442635326423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781442635326.jpg  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK